================================================================================
fragc
================================================================================

fragc is a tiny ShaderToy-like program in C for writing pixel shaders that run
on the CPU. You write a function that fulfills the frag() interface in a .c or
.cpp file and the processed image is displayed.

BUILDING
--------

Try running:
	$ build.bat <shader source>
and see what happens

HOT-LOADING
-----------

This doesn't work yet.

C++ OVERLOADS
-------------

The whole project should be able to be compiled with either clang or clang++
to allow the shaders to be written with +, -, *, / overloads for the vector and
matrix types. This makes writing the shaders more convenient and more similar to
writing GLSL.
